---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Product Naming"
  description="Understand GraceSoft product naming in plain business language: company name, product family, and function name."
>
  <main class="about-page">
    <section
      class="title-section services-hero relative isolate overflow-hidden text-white px-4 py-20 sm:py-24 lg:py-28"
    >
      <div
        class="container mx-auto max-w-5xl space-y-5 text-center reveal rise"
      >
        <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl leading-tight sm:text-4xl lg:text-6xl">
          How GraceSoft Product Names Work
        </h1>
        <p
          class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-sm text-gs-purple-100 sm:text-base lg:text-xl"
        >
          A simple naming system so business owners can immediately understand
          what each product is and what it does.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-problem-section px-4 py-14 sm:py-16 lg:py-20">
      <div class="container mx-auto max-w-6xl space-y-6 sm:space-y-8">
        <h2
          class="font-serif text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-center reveal rise"
        >
          The Naming Formula
        </h2>
        <div
          class="feature-card reveal rise delay-1 max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center space-y-4"
        >
          <p class="text-sm sm:text-base lg:text-lg text-gs-black-800">
            <strong>GraceSoft + Product Name + Function Name (optional)</strong>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm sm:text-base lg:text-lg text-gs-black-800">
            Think of it like an address:
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm sm:text-base lg:text-lg text-gs-black-800">
            1) GraceSoft = who built it, 2) Product Name = which product line it
            belongs to, 3) Function Name = what specific job it performs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-philosophy-section px-4 py-14 sm:py-16 lg:py-20">
      <div class="container mx-auto max-w-6xl space-y-8 sm:space-y-10">
        <h2
          class="font-serif text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-center reveal rise"
        >
          In Business Owner Language
        </h2>
        <div class="grid gap-4 sm:gap-5 grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3">
          <article
            class="process-step reveal rise delay-1 text-center space-y-3"
          >
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold sm:text-xl">GraceSoft</h3>
            <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gs-black-700">
              Company name. It tells you the maker and quality standard behind
              the product.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article
            class="process-step reveal rise delay-2 text-center space-y-3"
          >
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold sm:text-xl">Capture / Sentinel</h3>
            <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gs-black-700">
              Product name. It tells you which product family or suite this
              belongs to.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article
            class="process-step reveal rise delay-3 text-center space-y-3"
          >
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold sm:text-xl">Concierge</h3>
            <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gs-black-700">
              Function name. It tells you the exact role inside that product,
              like FAQ handling and booking.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-focus-section px-4 py-14 sm:py-16 lg:py-20">
      <div class="container mx-auto max-w-6xl space-y-8 sm:space-y-10">
        <h2
          class="font-serif text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-center reveal rise"
        >
          Examples
        </h2>
        <div class="grid gap-4 sm:gap-5 grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2">
          <article class="feature-card reveal rise delay-1 space-y-4">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold sm:text-2xl">GraceSoft Capture</h3>
            <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gs-black-700">
              GraceSoft = company name
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gs-black-700">
              Capture = product name
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gs-black-700">
              No extra function name is needed when the product name itself
              already describes the core purpose.
            </p>
            <p>
              <a
                href="https://capture.gracesoft.dev/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="capture-primary-link inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md px-5 py-3 font-semibold"
              >
                Visit GraceSoft Capture
              </a>
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="feature-card reveal rise delay-2 space-y-4">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold sm:text-2xl">
              GraceSoft Sentinel Concierge
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gs-black-700">
              GraceSoft = company name
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gs-black-700">
              Sentinel = product name (umbrella suite for all AI products)
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gs-black-700">
              Concierge = function name (FAQ and appointment booking AI agent)
            </p>
            <p>
              <a
                href="https://concierge.sentinel.gracesoft.dev/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="capture-primary-link inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md px-5 py-3 font-semibold"
              >
                Visit Sentinel Concierge
              </a>
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-credibility-section px-4 py-14 sm:py-16 lg:py-20">
      <div class="container mx-auto max-w-5xl space-y-6 sm:space-y-8">
        <h2
          class="font-serif text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-center reveal rise"
        >
          What Sentinel Concierge Does
        </h2>
        <ul class="about-credentials reveal rise delay-1">
          <li>
            Answers predefined FAQs using your approved response blueprint
          </li>
          <li>Handles appointment booking via WhatsApp chat flows</li>
          <li>Avoids non-business-hours booking windows</li>
          <li>Respects public holiday constraints in scheduling</li>
          <li>
            Supports calendar workflows based on Google, Apple, or Outlook
            calendars
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta-section px-4 py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24">
      <div
        class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl space-y-6 sm:space-y-8 text-center cta-panel reveal rise"
      >
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl leading-tight sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl">
          Need Concierge Customized for Your Team?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm sm:text-base lg:text-lg">
          We can adapt the FAQ blueprint, booking rules, and workflow
          integrations around your actual operations.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a
            href="/contact"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center font-semibold text-gs-purple-700 bg-white rounded-md px-5 py-3 shadow-sm transition-transform duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:opacity-90"
            >Talk to GraceSoft &rarr;</a
          >
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
